Just as you reach the archway, a piercing shriek fills the maze. Something is close. Too close.
With one final burst of speed, you throw yourself through the archway.
The moment you cross, the maze collapses behind you, swallowed into the earth.
You turn back—the Nightveil Hotel is gone.
But as you catch your breath, you feel something cold in your pocket.
You pull it out.\
The brass key.
And in the wind, barely audible—\
"You shouldn’t have left..."
